1:1|Darby|The word of Jehovah that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.
1:1|KJV|The word of the LORD that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.
1:1|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|耶和華的話臨到毘土珥的兒子約珥。
1:2|Darby|Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of  the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of  your fathers?
1:2|KJV|Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?
1:2|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|老年人哪，當聽這話；這地的一切居民哪，都要側耳聽。在你們的日子，或你們列祖的日子，曾發生這樣的事麼？
1:3|Darby|Tell your children of it, and [let] your children [tell]  their children, and their children another generation:
1:3|KJV|Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.
1:3|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|你們要將這事傳與子，子傳與孫，孫傳與後代。
1:4|Darby|that which the palmer-worm hath left hath the locust eaten;  and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten;  and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpillar  eaten.
1:4|KJV|That which the palmerworm hath left hath the locust eaten; and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten; and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpiller eaten.
1:4|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|剪蝗剩下的，群蝗來喫；群蝗剩下的，舔蝗來喫；舔蝗剩下的，毀蝗來喫。
1:5|Darby|Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of  wine, because of the new wine: for it is cut off from your  mouth.
1:5|KJV|Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine; for it is cut off from your mouth.
1:5|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|酒醉的人哪，要清醒哭泣；一切好酒的人哪，都要為新酒哀號；因為新酒從你們的口中斷絕了。
1:6|Darby|For a nation is come up upon my land, strong and without  number: his teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the  cheek teeth of a lioness.
1:6|KJV|For a nation is come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the cheek teeth of a great lion.
1:6|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|有一國民又強盛，又無數，上來侵犯我的地；其牙齒如獅子的牙齒，大牙如母獅的大牙。
1:7|Darby|He hath made my vine a desolation, and barked my fig-tree;  he hath made it clean bare, and cast it away: its branches are  made white.
1:7|KJV|He hath laid my vine waste, and barked my fig tree: he hath made it clean bare, and cast it away; the branches thereof are made white.
1:7|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|這民使我的葡萄樹荒廢，使我的無花果樹成為碎堆，剝盡樹皮而丟棄，使枝條露白。
1:8|Darby|Wail like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of  her youth.
1:8|KJV|Lament like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of her youth.
1:8|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|我的民哪，你當哀號，像處女腰束麻布，為幼年的丈夫哀號。
1:9|Darby|The oblation and the drink-offering are cut off from the  house of Jehovah; the priests, Jehovah's ministers, mourn.
1:9|KJV|The meat offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the LORD; the priests, the LORD's ministers, mourn.
1:9|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|素祭和奠祭從耶和華的殿中斷絕；事奉耶和華的祭司都悲哀。
1:10|Darby|The field is laid waste, the land mourneth; for the corn is  wasted, the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.
1:10|KJV|The field is wasted, the land mourneth; for the corn is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.
1:10|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|田荒廢，地悲哀；因為五穀毀壞，新酒乾竭，新油也缺乏。
1:11|Darby|Be ashamed, ye husbandmen; howl, ye vinedressers, for the  wheat and for the barley: because the harvest of the field hath  perished.
1:11|KJV|Be ye ashamed, O ye husbandmen; howl, O ye vinedressers, for the wheat and for the barley; because the harvest of the field is perished.
1:11|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|農夫阿，你們要慚愧；修理葡萄園的阿，你們要為大麥小麥哀號，因為田間的莊稼都滅絕了。
1:12|Darby|The vine is dried up, and the fig-tree languisheth; the  pomegranate-tree, the palm also and the apple-tree; all the  trees of the field are withered, yea, joy is withered away from  the children of men.
1:12|KJV|The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languisheth; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy is withered away from the sons of men.
