2:5|Darby|Like the noise of chariots, on the tops of the mountains,  they leap; like the noise of a flame of fire that devoureth the  stubble, as a strong people set in battle array.
2:5|KJV|Like the noise of chariots on the tops of mountains shall they leap, like the noise of a flame of fire that devoureth the stubble, as a strong people set in battle array.
2:5|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|在山頂蹦跳的響聲，如同車輛的響聲，如同火焰燒碎秸的響聲，又如同強盛的民擺陣豫備打仗。
2:6|Darby|Before them the peoples are in anguish: all faces turn pale.
2:6|KJV|Before their face the people shall be much pained: all faces shall gather blackness.
2:6|&#24674;&#24489;&#26412;|他們一出現，眾民翻絞痛苦，臉都變暗。
2:7|Darby|They run like mighty men; they climb the wall like men of  war; and they march every one on his ways, and break not their  ranks.
2:7|KJV|They shall run like mighty men; they shall climb the wall like men of war; and they shall march every one on his ways, and they shall not break their ranks:
